PV = C * [1 - (1 + r)^(-n)] / r

Where:
- PV is the present value (the value of the bond)
- C is the coupon payment per period
- r is the required stated annual return divided by 2 (since payments are made semiannually)
- n is the number of periods to maturity multiplied by 2 (since payments are made semiannually)

- Required stated semiannual return = Required stated annual return / 2 = 12% / 2 = 6%
